history.content: You should contact the professor for the IND ENG 195 class to see if they will make an exception for the time conflict to allow you to enroll. Otherwise, you need to DROP CS 188, enroll in IND ENG 195 and then re-enroll into CS 188. When one class allows a time conflict, that is the second class in which you need to enroll.

I am currently enrolled in 188 and on the waitlist for a class at the same time, Ind Eng 195. The course guide says that 188 allows for time conflicts but I keep getting emails saying that I’m unable to be enrolled in 195 off the waitlist because 188 doesn’t allow for time conflicts. Is there a way to resolve this or do I just have to wait?
history.subject: Time Conflict 188
